title: Pallbearer - 2006
description:
Pallbearer was an independent Canadian Metal band, from Toronto's Kensington Market, that formed in the fall of 2004, and continued through to Dec. of 2009. We had to stop playing due to physical and medical reasons involving 2 of the members.

Unfortunately we were unable to record our full length album due to the same reasons.

The demo, for all intents and purposes, was complete except for guitar solos.
I have included material, from the Jam session recordings, that would havwe been on the album. Sadly, there were also 3 other songs that I have no recording of at all.

*this is not the same Pallbearer that formed in the United States in 2010, and is a different sub-gerne of Metal.
